# Conventional Commits Template
# ==============================
# Format: <type>(<scope>): <description>
#
# Types:
#   feat:     New feature
#   fix:      Bug fix
#   docs:     Documentation only
#   refactor: Code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
#   test:     Adding or modifying tests
#   chore:    Build, dependencies, config changes
#   style:    Formatting, no logic change
#   perf:     Performance improvement
#
# Scope (optional):
#   lisa, max, anna, tom, sara (agents)
#   api, db, core, widget, dashboard (components)
#   calendar, email, knowledge, memory (services)
#
# Examples:
#   feat(lisa): add extract_lead_data tool with incremental scoring
#   fix(calendar): refresh token before creating event
#   docs(readme): add bilingual setup instructions
#   refactor(core): simplify agent loop error handling
#   test(api): add integration tests for WebSocket chat
#   chore(deps): update anthropic to 0.42.0
#
# Guidelines:
#   - Use imperative mood ("add" not "added")
#   - Keep first line under 72 characters
#   - Add body for complex changes (separated by blank line)
#   - Reference issues: "Closes #123" or "Refs #456"
#
# ==============================
